sql:
SELECT COALESCE(signal_value, 'N/A') AS NonNullSignalValue
FROM signal_strengths
WHERE device_id = 1;

SELECT COUNT(*)
FROM signal_strengths
WHERE signal_value < -70;

SELECT device_id, event_type, COUNT(*) AS event_count
FROM device_events
GROUP BY device_id, event_type;

external_knowledge:
- Gadgets refer to devices;
- Conference rooms refer to meeting rooms;
- Signal reception refers to signal strength in dBm.
